premise_source_doc_sentence: While the names of many of his later periods are debated , the most commonly accepted periods in his work are the Blue Period  (  1901 -- 1904  )  , the Rose Period  (  1904 -- 1906  )  , the African-influenced Period  (  1907 -- 1909  )  , Analytic Cubism  (  1909 -- 1912  )  , and Synthetic Cubism  (  1912 -- 1919  )  , also referred to as the Crystal period .

premise_source_doc_sentence: The Blue Period  (  Período Azul  )  is a term used to define the works produced by Spanish painter Pablo Picasso between 1901 and 1904 when he painted essentially monochromatic paintings in shades of blue and blue-green , only occasionally warmed by other colors .
